{"title":"Blindness resistance","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Blindness_resistance","type":"markdown","data":"**Blindness resistance** is a type of resistance [property](/wiki/Property \"Property\") that appears in *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")*.\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Description](#Description)\n- [2 Variants](#Variants)\n  - [2.1 dNetHack](#dNetHack)\n- [3 References](#References)\n\n## Description\n\nBlindness resistance prevents protects a [hero](/wiki/Hero \"Hero\") or [monster](/wiki/Monster \"Monster\") from light-related sources of [blindness](/wiki/Blindness \"Blindness\"):[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1)\n\n- The blinding [explosion attack](/wiki/Explosion_attack \"Explosion attack\") of a [yellow light](/wiki/Yellow_light \"Yellow light\")\n- The blinding [gaze attack](/wiki/Gaze_attack \"Gaze attack\") of an [Archon](/wiki/Archon \"Archon\")\n- The flash of an [expensive camera](/wiki/Expensive_camera \"Expensive camera\")\n- The blinding effects of [lightning](/wiki/Lightning \"Lightning\")\n- The blinding portion of the [magic trap](/wiki/Magic_trap \"Magic trap\") effect that creates monsters\n\nThe property can only be obtained via the following sources:[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2)\n\n- Being unconscious, blinded or [asleep](/wiki/Asleep \"Asleep\"), or being an [eyeless](/wiki/Eyeless \"Eyeless\") monster[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-3)\n- Being a monster that has a blinding explosion attack (i.e. a yellow light)[\\[4\\]](#cite_note-4)\n- Being a monster that has a blinding gaze attack (i.e. an Archon)[\\[5\\]](#cite_note-5)\n- [Wielding](/wiki/Wield \"Wield\") [Sunsword](/wiki/Sunsword \"Sunsword\")[\\[6\\]](#cite_note-6)[\\[7\\]](#cite_note-7)\n\nWearing [The Eyes of the Overworld](/wiki/The_Eyes_of_the_Overworld \"The Eyes of the Overworld\") does not grant blindness resistance, but overrides the effects of blindness and allows the wearer to see via [astral vision](/wiki/Astral_vision \"Astral vision\").\n\n## Variants\n\n### dNetHack\n\nIn [dNetHack](/wiki/DNetHack \"DNetHack\"), [notdNetHack](/wiki/NotdNetHack \"NotdNetHack\") and [notnotdNetHack](/wiki/NotnotdNetHack \"NotnotdNetHack\"), blindness resistance can apply to some other forms of blindness, and can be obtained from several other sources:\n\n- Wielding any of the [Artifacts of the Empyrial Lords](/wiki/DNetHack_artifacts#Artifacts_of_the_Empyrial_Lords \"DNetHack artifacts\")\n- [Invoking](/wiki/Invoking \"Invoking\") [The Shield of the All-Seeing](/wiki/DNetHack_artifacts#The_Shield_of_the_All-Seeing \"DNetHack artifacts\")\n\nA hero is completely immune to blindness while the [spirit](/wiki/Spirits_\\(dNetHack\\) \"Spirits (dNetHack)\") [Dantalion](/wiki/Dantalion \"Dantalion\") is bound, but only if they are not [wearing](/wiki/Wear \"Wear\") a [shirt](/wiki/Shirt \"Shirt\"), [suit](/wiki/Suit \"Suit\") or [cloak](/wiki/Cloak \"Cloak\") that covers the extra faces on their body.\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [src/mondata.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 146](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mondata.c#L146)\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [src/mondata.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 148](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mondata.c#L148)\n3. [↑](#cite_ref-3) [src/mondata.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 156](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mondata.c#L156)\n4. [↑](#cite_ref-4) [src/mondata.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 163](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mondata.c#L163)\n5. [↑](#cite_ref-5) [src/mondata.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 164](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mondata.c#L164)\n6. [↑](#cite_ref-6) [src/mondata.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 166](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mondata.c#L166)\n7. [↑](#cite_ref-7) [src/mondata.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 169](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mondata.c#L169)\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.](/images/f/f7/Nh367-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Blindness resistance - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Blindness_resistance\",\"wgTitle\":\"Blindness resistance\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":175507,\"wgRevisionId\":175507,\"wgArticleId\":40813,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Nethack-367 articles\",\"Properties\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Blindness_resistance\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":40813,\"wgRequestId\":\"b164361640d8277168fbf30c\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"u